#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:1
msgid "Vestax VCI-300"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:4
msgid ""
"The VCI-300 is a dedicated USB MIDI controller. It also comes with a built "
"in audio interface with standard 4-in/4-out and headphone connection, which "
"means all you need for DJing is the VCI-300, a laptop and a set of "
"headphones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:7
msgid ""
"This controller has been discontinued as Vestax went out of business in "
"2014."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:9
msgid ""
"[Forum thread](https://mixxx.discourse.group/t/vestax-vci-300mk-ii/11496)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:14
msgid "Differences between VCI-300 and VCI-300 MKII"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:17
msgid ""
"In 2010 Vestax made changes to the original VCI-300 that improved the "
"controller. There were *no* changes in the MIDI mapping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:19
msgid "Volume Boost (Gain Boost)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:22
msgid ""
"Higher output gain level and headphone volume level when supplying power "
"with the optional power adaptor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:23
msgid ""
"*Important Note:* Optional power supply DC-7 must be used in order to get "
"the boost on the headphones and main output. Without the power supply the "
"MKII will perform just like the original VCI-300. Also, using the DC-7 on "
"the original VCI-300 will do nothing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:26
msgid "Optional Vestax Digital Fader (not included)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:29
msgid ""
"The VCI-300MKII Cross fader can be upgraded to Vestax’s new magnetic sensor "
"system digital fader CF-X2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:31
msgid "New Direct Audio Thru"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:34
msgid ""
"Audio fed to the MIC/AUX input can now be directly sent to the main outputs "
"with the THRU switch turned ON, minimizing latency of when fed through ITCH."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:36
msgid "New adjust knobs for the JOG sensor control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:39
msgid ""
"New JOG sensor adjust knobs for speedy and accurate adjustments.the "
"VCI-300MKII’s JOG wheels have excellent tracking ability,and flexibility for"
" various play styles.You can control songs with analog precision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:42
msgid "New Mini Head-Phone Jack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:45
msgid ""
"The MKII features a 1/8 inch headphone connection along with standard 1/4 "
"inch connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:47
msgid "Mapping description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:50
msgid "Vestax VCI-300 (schematic view)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:57
msgid "Vestax VCI-300 (schematic view) Image (c) Vestax"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/vestax_vci_300.md:60
msgid ""
"Mixxx supports the VCI-300 out of the box. The mapping for Mixxx closely "
"resemble the original to make the transition easy."
msgstr ""

